diagram.documentation: The Internal Block Diagram (IBD) of the mission context provides a detailed representation of the relationships and conveyed items between the key elements involved in the mission, with the AOMS treated as a black box. This diagram illustrates how various mission components interact with each other to support the overall objectives of the mission. The IBD captures the flow of resources, data, and control signals between different mission blocks, ensuring a cohesive understanding of how the mission operates as an integrated system. By maintaining the AOMS as a black box, the IBD focuses on the mission-level interactions and dependencies, laying the groundwork for more detailed design and analysis in subsequent phases.
